# espeak-ng dictionary source for chemistry/biology pronunciation
#
# Format: each non-comment line is a `.replace` directive that rewrites
# the source token to a TTS-friendly form, which espeak-ng then phonemizes
# normally.
#
# This file is the source-of-truth for plugin v0.14.1+. Future updates will:
#   1. Compile this with `espeak-ng --compile=en` into a binary .dict
#   2. Drop the compiled file alongside Piper's bundled espeak-ng-data
#   3. Have Piper pick up the additional rules at synth time
#
# Until the compile/install flow is wired up, the regex + AI passes in
# reader.js handle this client-side. New terms added here should also be
# considered for the regex table in chemPreprocess() until espeak takes over.

.replace
# Chiral / stereo descriptors
d.r.        d r
d.r         d r
e.e.        e e
e.e         e e
e.r.        e r
e.r         e r

# Bioassay / pharmacology
IC50        I C fifty
EC50        E C fifty
LD50        L D fifty
GI50        G I fifty
TC50        T C fifty
pKa         p K a
pKi         p K i
Km          K m
Ki          K i
kcat        k cat
Vmax        V max
Hill        Hill

# Spectroscopy / instruments
NMR         N M R
1H          proton
13C         carbon thirteen
HSQC        H S Q C
HMBC        H M B C
NOESY       no-zee
COSY        co-zee
HPLC        H P L C
UPLC        U P L C
LCMS        L C M S
GCMS        G C M S
MALDI       MAL-dee
ESI         E S I
TOF         T O F
DFT         D F T
SAR         S A R

# Common chemical formulas (single elements + digit)
H2O         water
CO2         C O two
NaCl        sodium chloride
HCl         H C l
H2SO4       H two S O four
HNO3        H N O three
NaOH        sodium hydroxide
KOH         K O H
NH3         N H three
NH4         N H four
NaH         sodium hydride

# Transition metal halides (representative)
NiCl3       Ni C l three
NiCl2       Ni C l two
PdCl2       palladium chloride
CuCl        copper chloride
FeCl3       iron three chloride
ZnCl2       zinc chloride

# Solvents
DMSO        D M S O
DMF         D M F
THF         T H F
DCM         D C M
MeOH        methanol
EtOH        ethanol
iPrOH       I P A
tBuOH       tert-butanol

# Miscellaneous abbreviations
mol%        mole percent
v/v         volume per volume
w/w         weight per weight
w/v         weight per volume
DOI         D O I
PDB         P D B
RDKit       R D Kit
ADMET       AD-met
PAINS       pains
SMILES      smiles
